                <div class="content-area">

                    <!-- Left Content -->
                    <div class="left-panel">

                        <div class="card">
                            <h2 class="card-title">Description</h2>
                            <p>
                                Move beyond bin labeling (Phase 2) to checking actual usage. Conduct a surprise audit of a sample of 20 households to verify that they are correctly separating Wet (organic) and Dry (recyclable) waste. This task is crucial to solving the segregation problem.
                            </p>
                           
                        </div>

                        <div class="card">
                            <h2 class="card-title">Guidelines</h2>
                            <p>
                                <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i> After finishing forming your team, come together for a virtual ice breaker meet. <br> Here
                                you have to
                                click a virtual picture of the whole team together. <br>  <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i> Guidelines (How to Execute the Task): A small, designated NNCC team auditor must take random photo samples of bins before collection on a specified day. <br>  <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i> Compliance is based on the visible quality of the waste separation. <br>

                                <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i>Submission Guidelines: Submission via XL Sheet containing the audit results (Household ID vs. Segregation Status: Compliant/Non-Compliant) and a verification statement. <br>
                                
                                Final Point Checklist: <br>  <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i> Audit results for 20+ households. <br>  <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i> Photo proof of bin contents for a sample of 5 compliant and 5 non-compliant homes. <br>  <i class="ri-arrow-right-circle-line"></i> 80%+ compliance achieved. <br>
                                
                                Marking Scheme: <br>
                                
                                <strong>Team</strong>: 150 Pts for successful 20-home audit; 100 Pts bonus if compliance exceeds 80%. <br>
                                
                                <strong>Solo</strong>: 200 Pts for auditing 5 neighbors and providing clear, anonymous feedback/photos on their segregation status.
                            </p>
                         
                        </div>

                    </div>


                    <!-- Right Sidebar -->
                    <div class="right-panel">

                        <div class="card small">
